transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling, this is John, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Hi, my name is Martin Henchman and I ordered score blue.

Speaker 1: And I got to want to know when it's coming, one.

Speaker 2: And two, I think I ordered more and I can't see a receipt for that.

Speaker 1: And three, I think I made the wrong email address out.

Speaker 2: I can help you with all that. I just need your zip code, sir.

Speaker 1: 48038.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Okay, I got you pulled up here.

Speaker 2: So regarding the shipping, you will be approved probably today

Speaker 1: and then we'll ship it out within a day or two.

Speaker 2: We usually get it about a week after you ordered it.

Speaker 1: So you ordered it, it looks like, yesterday.

Speaker 2: So you probably will get it approximately next Monday.

Speaker 1: Our pharmacy is also in this storm zone, though, sort of like you.

Speaker 2: So it may be delayed with that.

Speaker 1: But typically, five to seven days after you order it, you receive it.

Speaker 2: Regarding your email, what should it be, sir?

Speaker 1: Yeah, my email.

Speaker 2: It's marty.henchman at gmail.com.

Speaker 1: And I left the dot out.

Speaker 2: Oh, so you didn't leave the dot out, sir.

Speaker 1: The way Google reads those emails, they actually read them the same,

Speaker 2: whether or not it has a period in there.

Speaker 1: So to not confuse our system, we automatically remove them.

Speaker 2: It still functions the same.

Speaker 1: You'll get emails all the same like you would, but it just doesn't display the period.

Speaker 2: Well, I checked it myself and it didn't work.

Speaker 1: I sent an email to myself.

Speaker 2: And I'm using Gmail, which is Google, you know.

Speaker 1: I understand.

Speaker 2: I'll send you an email explaining it because it does work.

Speaker 1: And then the last question was about the amount you ordered.

Speaker 2: You did order ten pills and then you added ten more.

Speaker 1: So you're getting 20 total pills.

Speaker 2: And then the total on that was $93.35.

Speaker 1: Have you taken the money yet?

Speaker 2: Yes, you were charged when you paid for them.

Speaker 1: I see.

Speaker 2: That's good.

Speaker 1: Sometimes I'm on limited funds.

Speaker 2: It depends when my checks come in.

Speaker 1: Isn't that where you get it paid for?

Speaker 2: Oh, I got you.

Speaker 1: Yeah, and if for some reason you were not approved, I don't expect that,

Speaker 2: because most people are not approved.

Speaker 1: That's very rare.

Speaker 2: But if it happens, you get your money back.

Speaker 1: So either way, you'll either get the pills or you'll get your money.

Speaker 2: But I got you.

Speaker 1: I'm looking at everything here.

Speaker 2: Are you telling me the doctor still hasn't approved me?

Speaker 1: When you put in that request to change your e-mail,

Speaker 2: that's a line to the doctor, not to customer service.

Speaker 1: So that then slows up the process, sir.

Speaker 2: Also, you did that on Sunday, so the doctor isn't even working Sunday.

Speaker 1: But, yes, he's going to approve you today.

Speaker 2: And it takes another week, huh?

Speaker 1: Where do you ship from?

Speaker 2: It ships out of Kentucky,

Speaker 1: and then it takes how long the U.S. Postal Service takes.

Speaker 2: And like I said, as you know, there's a ton of snow right now,

Speaker 1: so things are slowing down with that, too.

Speaker 2: Yeah, we got five inches overnight.

Speaker 1: Yeah, a lot of parts of the country got more than that, too,

Speaker 2: including where our pharmacy's at.

Speaker 1: So they will get this out this week, though.

Speaker 2: Thank you.
